          java.lang.Boolean _connectionReservation
          Specifies that the media stream channel(s) associated with the call being placed on hold be reserved for reuse at a later time. Optional.

          • False - channel(s) is not to be reserved (default).

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.AttachMediaService extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _connection

          ConnectionID _connection
          Specifies the connection at the attaching device. Mandatory.

        • _mediaServiceType

          MediaServiceType _mediaServiceType
          Specifies the requested media service type. Mandatory.

        • _mediaServiceVersion

          java.lang.Long _mediaServiceVersion
          Specifies the version of the media services. Optional.

        • _mediaServiceInstanceID

          java.lang.String _mediaServiceInstanceID
          Specifies the desired media service instance. Optional.

        • _connectionMode

          ConnectionMode _connectionMode
          Specifies the requested media service connection mode. Mandatory.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • consultationConference - conference the media access device (MAD) into the call via the Consultation Call and Conference Call models.
          • consultationConferenceHold - conference the MAD into the call via a Consultation Call and Hold Call models (the connection at the attaching device is placed on hold).
          • deflect - move the call from the attaching device to the MAD via the Deflect Call model.
          • directedPickup - direct the call from the attaching device to the MAD via the Directed Pickup Call model.
          • join - add a device into the call via the Join Call model. The application chooses which device is the MAD in the resulting conference.
          • singleStepConference - conference the MAD into the call via the Single Step Conference Call models.
          • singleStepConferenceHold - conference the MAD into the call via a Single Step Conference Call and Hold Call models (the connection at the attaching device is placed on hold).
          • singleStepTransfer - transfer that MAD into the call via the Single Step Transfer Call model.
          • transfer - transfer the MAD into the call via the Consultation Call and Transfer Call models.
          • direct - bind the media service instance directly to the existing connection at the attaching device.

        • _requestedConnectionState

          LocalConnectionState _requestedConnectionState
          Specifies the connection state in which the MAD will be at the time that the Media Attached event is generated. Optional.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.ButtonItem extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _button

          java.lang.String _button
          Specifies the button identifier (also known as the button address) of the button described by this entry. Mandatory.

        • _buttonLabel

          java.lang.String _buttonLabel
          Not supported.

        • _buttonLabelSettable

          java.lang.Boolean _buttonLabelSettable
          Not supported. Always false since the Set Button Information service is not yet supported.

        • _buttonFunction

          java.lang.String _buttonFunction
          The function assigned to the button. Always provided.

        • _buttonAssociatedNumber

          DeviceID _buttonAssociatedNumber
          Conditional. If the button has an associated extension, then that that extension is the content of this DeviceID. Otherwise, it is null. Note: The DeviceID in this parameter is in a different format than what is used in the rest of the API. It contains the associated button extension and is not a valid DeviceID that can be used in subsequent requests. The GetDeviceID or GetThirdPartyDeviceID requests in Device Services must be used to obtain a DeviceID that can be used in subsequent requests. The extension value returned by the getExtension method on this parameter can be used as the extension parameter in the GetDeviceID or GetThirdPartyDeviceID requests.

        • _buttonAssociatedNumberSettable

          java.lang.Boolean _buttonAssociatedNumberSettable
          Not supported.

        • _buttonPressIndicator

          java.lang.Boolean _buttonPressIndicator
          Not supported.

        • _lampList

          LampIDList _lampList
          List of LampIDs - These are the lamps that are associated with the button. There is always only one lampID and it is the same as the buttonID. The lamp is the green lamp. Red lamps are ignored. Always provided.

          ConnectionID _primaryOldCall
          Specifies the connection of the primary call. See Functional Implementation #1. Mandatory.

        • _secondaryOldCall

          ConnectionID _secondaryOldCall
          Specifies the connection of the secondary call. If the switching function supports the "fixed-view" option (as indicated by the capability exchange services), this parameter is mandatory.

          If the switching function supports the "local-view" option, this parameter is mandatory if there are two known calls involved with the conference (before the conference is created) from the perspective of the monitored device, otherwise it will not be provided.

          See CSTA Functional Requirements #1.

        • _conferencingDevice

          SubjectDeviceID _conferencingDevice
          Specifies the device ID of the conferencing device. Mandatory.

          This is of type SubjectDeviceID but note that SubjectDeviceID refers to a parameter type - not the subject device of the Conferenced event. This parameter type is used to represent the two devices in this event because the two devices are affected by the generation of this event (that is, the conferencing device and the addedParty device). However, there is only one device which is the subject of the event and that is the conferencing device. For more details on the SubjectDeviceID parameter type, see Subject Device Id

        • _addedParty

          SubjectDeviceID _addedParty
          Specifies the device ID of the last device added to the call. Mandatory.

          This is of type SubjectDeviceID but note that SubjectDeviceID refers to a parameter type - not the subject device of the Conferenced event. This parameter type is used to represent the two devices in this event because the two devices are affected by the generation of this event (that is, the conferencing device and the addedParty device). However, there is only one device which is the subject of the event and that is the conferencing device. For more details on the SubjectDeviceID parameter type, see Subject Device Id

        • _conferenceConnections

          ConnectionList _conferenceConnections
          Specifies information on each device/ConnectionID in the resulting conference call. Mandatory.

          See CSTA Functional Requirements #2.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.ConnectionListItem extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _newConnection

          ConnectionID _newConnection
          The CallID portion of this ConnectionID refers to the resulting call. This parameter is optional for the transferringDevice in the TransferedEvent, otherwise it is mandatory.

        • _oldConnection

          ConnectionID _oldConnection
          The CallID portion of this ConnectionID refers to the original call. This component is mandatory if the switching function previously reported the CallID, otherwise it is optional.

        • _endpoint

          Endpoint _endpoint
          For internal calls, this is the representation of the device inside the switching sub-domain. For external calls (incoming or outgoing) this is the representation of the externally located device (if known by the switching function). This component is a character string. The maximum length supported by the switching function is provided via the capabilities exchange services.
          It may be:
          • of any device identifier format.
          • of the following statuses: "Provided" " Not Known" "Restricted"

        • _associatedNID

          AssociatedNID _associatedNID
          For external calls (incoming and/or outgoing), this component specifies the Network Interface Device (for example, trunk, CO line) within the switching sub-domain that is associated with the externally located device. In that case the component endPoint DeviceID (if provided) will represent the externally located device. The associatedNID component is mandatory in case of external calls and will be omitted when the device is located inside the switching sub-domain.
          This component may be:
          • of any device identifier format
          • of the following statuses: "Provided" or "Not Known"

        • _resultingConnectionInfo

          ConnectionInformation _resultingConnectionInfo
          Contains the flow direction and channel characteristics associated with the resulting connection.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.DisplayListItem extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _displayID

          java.lang.String _displayID
          Indicates the display to which the other provided information applies. Mandatory.

        • _logicalRows

          java.lang.Long _logicalRows
          The number of rows on the logical display. Not supported.

        • _logicalColumns

          java.lang.Long _logicalColumns
          The number of columns on the logical display. Not supported.

        • _physicalRows

          java.lang.Long _physicalRows
          The number of rows on the physical display. When the number of physicalRows is equal to the number of logicalRows this parameter will be omitted, otherwise it will be present. Not supported

        • _physicalColumns

          java.lang.Long _physicalColumns
          The number of columns on the physical display. When the number of physicalColumns is equal to the number of logicalColumns this parameter will be omitted, otherwise it will be present. Not supported

        • _physicalBaseRowNumber

          java.lang.Long _physicalBaseRowNumber
          The row number of the physical base, this is the logical row that appears at the first row of the physical display. When the number of physicalRows is equal to the number of logicalRows this parameter will be omitted, otherwise it will be present. Not supported

        • _physicalBaseColumnNumber

          java.lang.Long _physicalBaseColumnNumber
          The column number of the physical base. To be specific, the logical column that appears at the first column of the physical display. When the number of physicalColumns is equal to the number of logicalColumns this parameter will be omitted, otherwise it will be present. Not supported

        • _characterSet

          CharacterSet _characterSet
          Specifies the character set which is being used to represent the text on the display.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • ASCII (default)
          • Unicode
          • Proprietary
          Optional. Not supported

        • _contentsOfDisplay

          java.lang.String _contentsOfDisplay
          Specifies the text on display as a string of characters consisting of the text on each row of the display (including spaces) concatenated together. The contentsOfDisplay parameter always contains the maximum number of characters on the display as indicated by the number of logicalRows and logicalColumns. Mandatory.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.IntrudeCall extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _intrude

          ConnectionID _intrude
          Specifies the connection of the calling device. Mandatory.

        • _participationType

          ParticipationType _participationType
          Specifies the type of participation the added device has in the resulting call. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • active (default) - The added device actively participates in the resulting conference call.
          • silent - The added device can listen but cannot actively participate in the resulting conference call.
          • none - The added device cannot actively participate in the resulting conference call. As a result, the flow direction of the added devices's connection will be None.

          If the switching function only supports "Case B" of the service and the participationType parameter is supplied, then the service will be rejected by the switching function.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.JoinCall extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _activeCall

          ConnectionID _activeCall
          Specifies an existing connection in an active call to which the new device is to be added (or joined). Mandatory.

        • _joiningDevice

          DeviceID _joiningDevice
          Specifies the device that is to be added to (join) the existing call. Mandatory.

        • _autoOriginate

          AutoOriginate _autoOriginate
          Specifies if the joining device is to be prompted or not (handsfree mode). Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • Prompt (default)
          • Do Not Prompt (auto originate)

        • _participationType

          ParticipationType _participationType
          Specifies the type of participation the joining device has in the resulting call. Optional.

          This is one of the following:

          • active (default) - the joining device actively participates in the resulting conference call. As a result, the flow direction of the joiningDevice's connection (that is, conferencedCall) will be Transmit and Receive.
          • silent - the joining device can listen but cannot actively participate in the resulting conference call. As a result, the flow direction of the joiningDevice's connection (that is, conferencedCall) will be Receive.
          • none - the joining device cannot actively participate in the resulting conference call. As a result, the flow direction of the joiningDevice's connection (that is, conferencedCall) will be None.

          • 3 - Green
          • 4 - Blue

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.LampModeEvent extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _monitorCrossRefID

          java.lang.String _monitorCrossRefID
          Field _monitorCrossRefID

        • _device

          SubjectDeviceID _device
          Specifies the device where the lamp mode status was changed. Mandatory.

        • _lamp

          java.lang.String _lamp
          Specifies the lamp identifier of the lamp on the device. Lamp identifier is a string. If the lamp has an associated button, the lamp ID and the button ID are the same. Mandatory.

        • _lampLabel

          java.lang.String _lampLabel
          Specifies the label by which the lamp may be referenced. Not supported.

        • _lampMode

          java.lang.Short _lampMode
          Specifies how the lamp is lit. Mandatory.

          A value from 0 - 100 specifying how the lamp is lit (flutter, off, steady, etc.)

        • _lampBrightness

          LampBrightness _lampBrightness
          Indicates the intensity of the lamp if it is on (as indicated by lampMode parameter). Actual visible brightness levels are lamp-dependent. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • Unspecified/Normal (default)
          • Dim
          • Bright

        • _lampColor

          java.lang.Short _lampColor
          A value from 0 - 100 specifying the color of the lamp. Mandatory.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.MakePredictiveCall extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _callingDevice

          DeviceID _callingDevice
          Specifies the device on behalf of which the call is originated. Mandatory.

        • _calledDirectoryNumber

          DeviceID _calledDirectoryNumber
          Specifies the called device. Mandatory.

        • _signallingDetection

          SignallingDetection _signallingDetection
          Specifies the switching function actions to be taken when the specified call progress conditions at the called device or network are met. Optional.

          It includes the following components:

          • [AVAYA QUALIFIED] signallingCondition (M) Enumerated - Specifies the conditions that must be satisfied before the switching function processes the signallingConditionsAction. This product supports callEstablished only. The complete set of possible values is:
            • callDelivered - Not supported.
            • callEstablished - Process the specified actions when the call has been answered at the called device.
          • signallingConditionsAction (M) Enumerated - Action to be taken by the switching function upon detecting a signallingCondition. The complete set of possible values is:
            • destinationDetection - The conditions/actions specified in the destinationDetection parameter should be followed.
            • remainConnected - The called device is to remain in the call and the connection to the calling device is attempted.

        • _destinationDetection

          DestinationDetection _destinationDetection
          Specifies the switching function actions to be taken when the specified signallingCondition at the called device is met. Optional.

          Each entry in the list contains the following:

          • destinationCondition (M) Enumerated - Specifies the condition that must be satisfied before the switching function processes the detectionAction. The complete set of possible values is:
            • humanVoice - Process the specified actions when a human voice is detected at the called device.
            • answeringMachine - Process the specified actions when an answering machine is detected at the called device.
            • facsimileMachine - Process the specified actions when a (FAX) machine or modem is detected at the called device.
          • detectionAction (M) Enumerated - Action to be taken by the switching function upon detecting of a particular destination condition. The complete set of possible values is:
            • clearCalledConnection - The connection for the called device is to be cleared.
            • remainConnected - The called device is to remain in the call and the connection to the calling device is attempted.

          Note that if multiple entries are provided, the switching function will process the detectionAction associated with the first destinationCondition that is detected.

        • _defaultAction

          DetectionAction _defaultAction
          Specifies the actions to be taken when the switching function determines that the condition specified in the signallingCondition component cannot be met. Optional.

          The complete list of possible values is:

          • clearCalledConnection - The connection for the called device is to be cleared.
          • remainConnected - The called device is to remain in the call and the connection to the calling device is attempted.

        • _accountCode

          byte[] _accountCode
          Field _accountCode

        • _authCode

          byte[] _authCode
          Field _authCode

        • _autoOriginate

          AutoOriginate _autoOriginate
          Specifies if the calling device's connection is automatically answered (hands-free mode). Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • prompt (default)
          • doNotPrompt (auto originate)

        • _alertTime

          java.lang.Long _alertTime
          Specifies the amount of time, in seconds, the called device is to be alerted before the call is cleared. This product supports alertTime values in the range of 12-90 seconds. Optional.

          SubjectDeviceID _invokingDevice

        • _auditoryApparatus

          java.lang.String _auditoryApparatus
          Specifies the auditory apparatus containing the microphone whose gain has changed. Mandatory.

        • _microphoneGain

          MicrophoneGain _microphoneGain
          Specifies the gain as an absolute gain value or that the gain has been incremented or decremented by a switch specified increment. Mandatory.

          It may be one of the following possible choices:

          • micGainAbs (Value) - Specifies a value from 0 through 100. 0 indicates silence, and 100 indicates maximum gain. The granularity and quantization of the values 1 though 99 are device specific
          • micGainInc (Enumerated) - Specifies if the gain was incremented or decremented by a switch specified amount. The complete set of possible values is:
            • increment - the gain value was incremented
            • decrement - the gain value was decremented.

          MonitorObject _monitorObject
          Specifies the monitor object of a call or device to be monitored. Mandatory.

          This will be one of the following choices:

          • call (ConnectionID) - Specifies a call (connection) object.
          • device (DeviceID) - Specifies a device object.

        • _monitorExistingCalls

          java.lang.Boolean _monitorExistingCalls
          Indicates whether or not the computing function will receive event reports regarding calls that are currently existing at the device at which the monitor was started. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • TRUE - Indicates event reports will be provided for calls that are at the device at the time of the acknowledgement [Default].
          • FALSE - Indicates event reports will not be provided for calls that are at the device at the time of the acknowledgement.
          This parameter is applicable to monitors that have devices as their object. For such monitors, if this parameter is not present (or the parameter is not supported), it means that the switching function always provides event reports for calls that are currently present at the device when the monitor was started.

        • _progressIndicator

          ProgressIndicator _progressIndicator
          Specifies an interworking situation encountered in the public or private network outside the switching sub-domain. As a consequence of entering the network, the level of event reporting associated with this call may be reduced.

          This parameter consists of the following components:

          1. progressLocation (M) - It may be one of the following:
            • User
            • Private network serving the local user
            • Public network serving the local user
            • Transit network
            • Public network serving the remote user
            • Private network serving the remote user
            • Local interface controlled by the signalling link
            • International Network
            • Network beyond interworking point
            • Other
          2. progressDescription (M) - It may be one of the following:
            • ISDN Progress Description - This information is derived from ETSI ETS 300 182: 1993.
            • QSIG Progress Description - This information is derived from ECMA-143.
            • Other

          1. networkType (M) - The complete set of possible values is:
            • ISDN public
            • Non-ISDN public

            • Other
          2. eventsProvided (O) - This is a bitmap of all of the Call Control events defined in this Standard. The call control events are specified in ECMA 269, section 17.2, Table 17-143 "Call Control Events Summary".

        • _networkCapability

          NetworkCapability _networkCapability
          Specifies the type of network reached and the Call Control events supported by the network.

          It includes the following components:

          1. networkType (M) - The complete set of possible values is:
            • ISDN public
            • Non-ISDN public
            • ISDN private
            • Non-ISDN private
            • Other
          2. eventsProvided (O) - This is a bitmap of the Call Control events defined in this Standard.

        • _calledDevice

          CalledDeviceID _calledDevice
          Field _calledDevice

        • _originatingDevice

          DeviceID _originatingDevice
          Specifies the originating device. The originating device represents a device that originated a call in the switching subdomain on behalf of the calling device (for example, a group of stations). The originating device will not represent a Network Interface Device.

          This parameter may be provided for external outgoing and internal calls when the originating device is different from the calling device.

          This parameter will not be provided for external incoming calls or when the originating device is identical to the calling device.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.PlayMessage extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _messageToBePlayed

          java.lang.String _messageToBePlayed
          Specifies the numeric filename of the message to be played. Do not include the ".wav" suffix for a numeric filename; it will be automatically appended. Neither a full directory path nor a subpath can be included with the filename. To specify an alphanumeric filename, a relative path with the filename, or a list of files, set messageToBePlayed to "0" and specify the alphanumeric filename in extensions playMessage. Mandatory.

        • _overConnection

          ConnectionID _overConnection
          Specifies the connection on which the message is to be played. Only the deviceID field of the connectionID is used. Mandatory.

        • _duration

          java.lang.Long _duration
          Specifies the length of time to play the message in milliseconds. If set to zero, then the play service will immediately terminate and a StopEvent will be generated. If the duration is shorter than the length of the message, then the message will be played until duration is met. If the message length is less than the duration parameter, then the message will be played only once. Optional

        • _termination

          TerminatingConditions _termination
          The DTMF digit detection termination condition is supported. If this is set, the recording will continue until a DTMF digit is detected on the device.

          Specifies the list of conditions that cause the playback to terminate.

          This may include one or more of the following actions:

          • duration exceeded (this value can only be provided if the duration parameter is provided)
          • DTMF digit (external to the message being played) detected
          • end of message detected
          • speech (external to the message being played) detected.
          Optional.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.QueryVoiceAttribute extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _messageToQuery

          java.lang.String _messageToQuery
          Specifies the message whose attribute is to be queried. Mandatory.

        • _resource

          java.lang.String _resource
          Field _resource

        • _attributeToQuery

          AttributeToQuery _attributeToQuery
          Specifies the attribute to be queried. Mandatory.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • encoding algorithm - requests the encoding algorithm used for the specified message.
          • sampling rate - requests the sampling rate used for the specified message.
          • duration - requests the duration (in milliseconds) of the specified message.
          • file name - requests the (implementation-specific) name of the specified message.
          • current position* - requests the value of the position pointer (in milliseconds after the beginning of the message).
          • current speed* - requests the current playing speed of the specified message.
          • current volume* - requests the current playing volume of the specified message.
          • current level* - requests the current recording level of the specified message.
          • current state* - requests the current state of the specified message.
          * indicates that this attribute can only be requested if the connection parameter is provided.

        • _connection

          ConnectionID _connection
          Specifies the connection of the message whose attribute is being queried. Optional.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.QueryVoiceAttributeResponse extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _attribute

          AttributeInfo _attribute
          Specifies the value of the specified attribute. Mandatory.

          May be one of the following (choice depends upon the attribute specified in the service request):

          • encodingAlgorithm (Enumerated) - encoding algorithm used for the specified message. The complete set of possible values is:
            • ADPCM6K
            • ADPCM8K
            • muLawPCM6k
            • aLawPCM6K
          • samplingRate (Value) used for the specified message.
          • duration (Value) in milliseconds of the specified message.
          • filename (Characters) implementation specific name of the specified message.
          • currentPosition (Value) in the message (milliseconds from the beginning of the message).
          • currentSpeed (Value) of the message (represents the percentage of normal speed, with 100% being normal speed and the slowest reportable speed being 1%).
          • currentVolAbs (Value 0..100) - absolute play volume of the message (100 indicating maximum volume and 0 indicating silence).
          • currentGain (Value 0..100) gain at which the message was recorded (100 indicating maximum level and 0 indicating minimum level).
          • current state (Enumerated) - a Voice Unit state. The complete set of possible states is:
            • stop
            • play
            • record
            • suspend play
            • suspend record
            • review
            Refer to ECMA-269, Figure 6-21, "Voice Unit Operational Model" in section 6.2.1 for a description of the states.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

          Specifies the resulting Message Identifier. Mandatory. If the application chose to default the filename to timestamp extension.wav, then this field specifies the resulting Wave file name (with timestamp and extension) without the ".wav" suffix. The file is placed on the connector server. A ".wav" needs to be appended to a numeric filename to get the complete filename as stored on the disk. If the application instead specified its own filename in the request's RecordMessagePrivateData, then this field is "0" and the file name is returned in the response's extension in RecordMessageResponsePrivateData.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.RingerStatusEvent extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _monitorCrossRefID

          java.lang.String _monitorCrossRefID
          Field _monitorCrossRefID

        • _device

          SubjectDeviceID _device
          Specifies the device where the ring status was changed. Mandatory.

        • _ringer

          java.lang.String _ringer
          Specifies the ringerID associated with the device. Always set to "0000" since there is only one ringer. Mandatory.

        • _ringMode

          RingMode _ringMode
          Indicates if the ringer is in an active ring cycle. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • ringing - The ringer is ringing (provided when either the ringer is physically ringing or is in the "quiet phase" of a ring cycle).
          • not ringing - The ringer is not in an active ring cycle.

        • _ringCount

          java.lang.Integer _ringCount
          Indicates the number of complete ring cycles that the ringer has been ringing. The values 0-999 indicate the actual number of complete ring cycles. The value of 1000 indicates that a value greater than 999 was reached. Optional.

        • _ringPattern

          java.lang.Long _ringPattern
          Indicates the ringing pattern of the ringer. The meaning of the ringing pattern and the number of ringing patterns is device specific. In order to decode this value for Avaya IP endpoints, use the com.avaya.csta.phsyical.RingerPatternConstants class. Optional.

        • _ringVolume

          Volume _ringVolume
          Indicates the ring volume as an absolute value or that the volume was incremented or decremented by a switch specified increment. The ring volume is associated with the ringer until reset by the switching function or until reset by the Set Ringer Status service. Optional.

          It may be one of the following possible choices:

          • ringVolAbs (Value) - Specifies a value from 0 through 100. 0 indicates silence, and 100 indicates maximum volume. The granularity and quantization of the values 1 though 99 are device specific.
          • ringVolInc (Enumerated) - Specifies if the volume was incremented or decremented by a switch specified amount. The complete set of possible values is:
            • increment - the volume was incremented.
            • decrement - the volume was decremented.

          Note that the relationship between the ringer volume and loudness is ringer specific.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.RingerStatusItem extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _ringer

          java.lang.String _ringer
          Indicates the ringerID. Mandatory.

        • _ringMode

          RingMode _ringMode
          Indicates if the ringer is in a ringing cycle.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • ringing - The ringer is ringing (provided when either the ringer is physically ringing or is in the quiet phase of a ring cycle).
          • not ringing - The ringer is not being rung.
          Mandatory.

        • _ringCount

          java.lang.Integer _ringCount
          Not supported. Indicates the value (0...1000) of the number of complete ring cycles that the ringer has been, or was, ringing. The values 0-999 indicate the actual number of complete ring cycles. The value of 1000 indicates that a value greater than 999 was reached. Optional.

        • _ringPattern

          java.lang.Long _ringPattern
          Indicates the value of the ringing pattern of the ringer. The meaning of ringing patterns and the number of supported patterns is device specific. The ring pattern is associated with the ringer until reset by the switching function or until reset by the Set Ringer Status request. Optional.

        • _ringVolAbs

          java.lang.Integer _ringVolAbs
          Not supported. Indicates the absolute volume level (0...100) of the ringer. The ring volume is associated with the ringer until reset by the switching function or until reset by the Set Ringer Status service. A value of 0 indicates silence, and 100 indicates maximum volume. The granularity and quantization of the values 1 though 99 are device specific. If this component is not provided, the absolute ringer volume is unknown. Note that the relationship between the ringer volume and loudness is ringer specific. Optional.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.RingerStatusList extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _ringerStatusItemList

          java.util.Vector<E> _ringerStatusItemList
          Specifies information about the specified ringer, including state, cycles, pattern, and volume. This is of type RingerStatusItem. See RingerStatusItem for more information and a description of the components.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.SetDisplay extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _device

          DeviceID _device
          Specifies the device's physical element. Mandatory.

        • _display

          java.lang.String _display
          Specifies which display on the physical device needs to be set. If the device has only one display this parameter may be omitted, but it may also be filled in (specifying the one and only displayID). If the device has more than one display this parameter will be present.

        • _physicalBaseRowNumber

          java.lang.Long _physicalBaseRowNumber
          The row number of the physical base, that is, the logical row that appears at the first row of the physical display. This parameter may be omitted or may be present when it needs to be changed. The parameter will be omitted when it is not relevant because the number of physical rows is equal to the number of logical rows. Optional.

        • _physicalBaseColumnNumber

          java.lang.Long _physicalBaseColumnNumber
          The column number of the physical base, that is, the logical column that appears at the first column of the physical display. This parameter may be omitted or may be present when it needs to be changed. This parameter will be omitted when it is not relevant because the number of physical columns is equal to the number of logical columns. Optional.

        • _contentsOfDisplay

          java.lang.String _contentsOfDisplay
          Specifies the text to place on the display as a string of characters consisting of the text on each row of the display (including spaces) concatenated together. If a null string is sent, the display will be cleared. Mandatory.

        • _offset

          java.lang.Long _offset
          Specifies the offset, in number-of-characters (not bytes in the characters-to-be-displayed message string), where text is to start on the display.

          Allowed values are from zero (default) to (MaxNbrOfLogicalColumns * MaxNbrOfLogicalRows - 1). Non-printable characters (for example, Carriage Return (CR), Line Feed (LF), and Tab) are counted in determining offsets and the message length. Optional.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.SetLampMode extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _device

          DeviceID _device
          Specifies the device's physical element. Mandatory.

        • _lamp

          java.lang.String _lamp
          Specifies the lampID of the lamp on the device. Mandatory.

        • _lampMode

          java.lang.Short _lampMode
          Specifies how the lamp associated with the specified device should be lit. Mandatory.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • 0 - Brokenflutter. Superposition of wink and flutter.
          • 1 - Flutter. Fast on and off.
          • 2 - Off. Lamp is off.
          • 3 - Steady. Lamp is continuously lit.
          • 4 - Wink. Lamp is winking.
          • 5 - not used
          • All other values (6-100) are switching function specific.

        • _lampBrightness

          LampBrightness _lampBrightness
          Indicates intensity of lamp when the lamp is on (as indicated by lampMode parameter). Actual visible brightness levels are lamp-dependent. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • Unspecified/Normal (default)
          • Dim
          • Bright

        • _lampColor

          java.lang.Short _lampColor
          Specifies the color of the lamp. Optional.

          The meaning of the following values are pre-assigned:

          • 0 - no color
          • 1 - Red
          • 2 - Yellow
          • 3 - Green
          • 4 - Blue
          • 5 - not used
          • All other values (6-100) are switching function specific.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

          MicrophoneGain _microphoneGain
          Specifies the gain as an absolute gain value or that the gain should be incremented or decremented by a switch specified increment. Mandatory.

          • micGainAbs (Value) - Specifies a value from 0 through 100. 0 indicates silence, and 100 indicates maximum gain. The granularity and quantization of the values 1 though 99 are device specific
          • micGainInc (Enumerated) - Specifies if the gain is to be incremented or decremented by a switch specified amount. The complete set of possible values is:
            • increment - the gain value is incremented
            • decrement - the gain value is decremented.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.SetRingerStatus extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _device

          DeviceID _device
          Specifies the device's physical element. Mandatory.

        • _ringer

          java.lang.String _ringer
          Specifies the ringer to be set. Mandatory.

        • _ringMode

          RingMode _ringMode
          Indicates if the ringer should be rung or not rung. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • ringing - The ringer should be rung.
          • not ringing - The ringer should not be rung.

        • _ringPattern

          java.lang.Long _ringPattern
          Indicates the value of the ringing pattern of the ringer. The meaning of the ringing patterns and the number of supported patters is device specific. This parameter is only valid when ringMode has a value of ringing and has no effect on the ringPattern used during subsequent call related ringing.

          If ringMode has a value of Ringing then ringPattern is Mandatory.

        • _ringVolume

          Volume _ringVolume
          Indicates the volume level of the ringer. May specify either an absolute value or may specify that the volume should be incremented or decremented by a switch specified increment. Optional.

          It may be one of the following possible choices:

          • ringVolAbs (Value) - Specifies a value from 0 through 100. 0 indicates silence, and 100 indicates maximum volume. The granularity and quantization of the values 1 though 99 are device specific
          • ringVolInc (Enumerated) - Specifies if the volume is to be incremented or decremented by a switch specified amount. The complete set of possible values is:
            • increment - the volume is incremented
            • decrement - the volume is decremented.

          Note that the relationship between the ringer volume and loudness is ringer specific.

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

      • Serialized Fields

        • _connection

          ConnectionID _connection
          Specifies the Connection on which the voice attribute should be set. Mandatory.

        • _message

          java.lang.String _message
          Specifies the message whose voice attribute is to be set. This parameter is mandatory if there are multiple active messages on the specified connection, otherwise the parameter is optional.

          If this parameter is not provided, the service applies to the currently active message on the specified connection.

        • _resource

          java.lang.String _resource
          Field _resource

        • _attributeToSet

          AttributeToSet _attributeToSet
          Specifies the attribute to be set. Mandatory.

          This will be one of the following choices:

          • currentSpeed (Value) - sets the playing speed of the message (represents the percentage of normal speed, with 100% being normal speed and the slowest reportable speed being 1%)
          • currentVolume (Choice Structure) - sets the playing volume of the message. May specify either an absolute value or may specify that the volume should be incremented or decremented by a implementation specified increment. It may be one of the following possible choices:
            • currentVolAbs (Value) - Specifies a value from 0 through 100. 0 indicates silence, and 100 indicates maximum volume. The granularity and quantization of the values 1 though 99 are device specific.
            • currentVolInc (Enumerated) - Specifies if the volume is to be incremented or decremented by a switch specified amount. The complete set of possible values is:
              • increment - the volume is incremented
              • decrement - the volume is decremented.
          • currentGain (Value 0..100) - sets the recording gain of the message (100 indicating maximum level and 0 indicating minimum level)

      • Serialized Fields

        • _activeCall

          ConnectionID _activeCall
          Specifies an existing connection in the call to which a new device is to be added. Mandatory.

          Specifies the device that is to be added to the call. Mandatory.

        • _participationType

          ParticipationType _participationType
          Specifies the type of participation the added device has in the resulting call. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • Active (default) - The added device actively participates in the resulting conference call. As a result, the flow direction of the deviceToJoin's connection (that is, conferencedCall) will be Transmit and Receive.

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.StartDataCollection extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _object

          CallObject _object
          Specifies the object to which a data collection should be initiated. Mandatory.

          This will be one of the following choices:

          • device (DeviceID) - specifies the device upon which the data collection is to be started. Data collection occurs on the next connection at this device and is stopped when this connection is cleared. If there are one or more calls at this device and this choice is selected, then this service request will be rejected.
          • call (ConnectionID) - specifies a specific call (connection) upon which the data collection is to be started.

        • _dataCollType

          DataCollType _dataCollType
          Specifies the data-type of the data collection. Optional.

          The complete set of possible values is:

          • digits - DTMF/rotary pulse digits
          • telephonyTones - telephony tones

        • _digitsReportingCriteria

          DigitsReportingCriteria _digitsReportingCriteria
          Specifies the criteria associated with the reporting of the DTMF/rotary pulse digits. This value may be provided only when the dataCollType value is Digits. Optional.

          This parameter consists of the following components:

          • numChars (C) Value - specifies the number of characters to collect before sending the Data Collected message with the collected digit characters.
          • flushChar (C) Character(1) - specifies an ASCII (IA5) character that, if detected, causes any previously unreported digit characters (including this character) to be sent in the Data Collected service.
          • timeout (C) Value - specifies a duration, in milliseconds, when any previously unreported digit characters are sent in the Data Collected service.
          If this parameter is provided, at least one component must be provided.

        • _extensions

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

      • Serialized Fields

        • _sysStatRegisterID

          java.lang.String _sysStatRegisterID
          Field _sysStatRegisterID

        • _actualStatusFilter

          StatusFilter _actualStatusFilter
          Specifies the actual set of System Status Types that will be filtered (not sent) by the switching function.

          This parameter is a bitmap with the same set of possible values as in the service request.

          The actual types filtered may differ from what was requested in the service request (See CSTA Functional Implementation #5).

          If the requestType parameter in the service request includes System Status, then this parameter is mandatory, otherwise it will not be provided.

          CSTACommonArguments _extensions
          Field _extensions

    • Class ch.ecma.csta.binding.VoiceAttributeChangedEvent extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _monitorCrossRefID

          java.lang.String _monitorCrossRefID
          Field _monitorCrossRefID

        • _connection

          ConnectionID _connection
          Indicates the connection for the message whose attribute has changed. Mandatory.

        • _message

          java.lang.String _message
          Indicates the message that has changed. Mandatory.

        • _resource

          java.lang.String _resource
          Field _resource

        • _playVolume

          Volume _playVolume
          Indicates the current play volume as an absolute value or that the volume was incremented or decremented by a switch specified increment. Optional.

          It may be one of the following possible choices:

          • playVolAbs (Value) - Specifies a value from 0 through 100. 0 indicates silence, and 100 indicates maximum volume. The granularity and quantization of the values 1 though 99 are device specific.
          • playVolInc (Enumerated) - Specifies if the volume was incremented or decremented by a switch specified amount. The complete set of possible values is:
            • increment - the volume was incremented
            • decrement - the volume was decremented.

        • _recordingGain

          java.lang.Integer _recordingGain
          Indicates the current recording level (100 indicating maximum gain and 0 indicating minimum gain). Optional.

        • _speed

          java.lang.Long _speed
          Indicates the current playing speed of the message (represents the percentage of normal speed, with 100% being normal speed and the slowest reportable speed being 1%)

        • _currentPosition

          java.lang.Long _currentPosition
          Indicates the number of milliseconds from the start of the message. Optional.
